programme.title: Paranormal State: Dark Man
programme.desc: A grieving mother suspects her deceased son may have fallen victim to a mysterious entity called The Dark Man.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Vegas
programme.desc: The PRS travels to Sin City to investigate a 14-year old medium who claims to speak to a dead girl.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Cemetery
programme.desc: PRS visits a gothic graveyard, where a jealous spirit seems to be preying on the newlywed wife of the cemetery's caretaker. Ryan traces the haunting to a mysterious, unclaimed cremation urn on the grounds.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Fire
programme.desc: Christina has been experiencing paranormal activity ever since her father and step-mother were murdered near Columbus, OH last year. PRS and psychic/medium?Chip Coffey delve into a open murder case and wind up exposing a family divide.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Good Vs. Evil
programme.desc: PRS visits a western Pennsylvania couple wracked by a torrent of paranormal activity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Family Ties
programme.desc: Jimmie is haunted by the apparition of a mysterious old woman who peers at him in the bathroom of his family's Petersburg, VA home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Room & Board
programme.desc: The owners of a vacation lodge in the remote town of North Hudson, NY, feel their woodsy getaway is plagued by negative spirits.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Lady Vampire
programme.desc: PRS investigates a case involving single mom, Dawn, and her 5-year-old daughter, both of whom are tormented by the appearance of a hag they call "lady vampire."

programme.title: Paranormal State: Return of the Dead: Glove II
programme.desc: PRS returns to the site of one of their most famous cases, Daisytown, PA, where they had discovered a glove print of an old miner that they determined was the spirit of a Great-Grandfather.
programme.sub-title: Return of the Dead: Glove II

programme.title: Paranormal State: Haunted Homecoming
programme.desc: Ryan brings PRS to his hometown of Sumter, SC to investigate a chilling case where a young boy was tragically shot and killed on a front doorstep while trick-or-treating on Halloween.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Mothman
programme.desc: Ryan takes his team to Point Pleasant, West Virginia to investigate his own personal holy grail of paranormal lore: the mysterious Mothman.

programme.title: Paranormal State: First Contact
programme.desc: Washington State, a hotbed of unexplained paranormal activity. Between possible UFOs in the sky and winged creatures in the woods, Ryan and his team are forced to face their fears and deal with the question: Are we truly alone in the universe?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Vendetta
programme.desc: P.R.S. investigates claims of supernatural revenge in the Pennsylvania Poconos. When a client's new boyfriend moves in, does the paranormal move in with him? Or did her ex put a hex on her house and the entire family?

programme.title: Most Haunted: Oldham Coliseum Theatre, Lancashire
programme.desc: The team visits Oldham Coliseum, one of the Northwest's oldest theatres and the scene of a young actor's tragic death. Thought to roam here, will he choose tonight to make his presence known?

programme.title: Most Haunted: Ancient Ram Inn, Wotton-under-Edge, Gloucestershire
programme.desc: Witchcraft, human sacrifice and an incubus await the team at the Ancient Ram Inn. Feeling less than welcome, the team's apprehensions will ultimately turn into terror with violent repercussions.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Pleasley Vale Mills, Nottinghamshire
programme.desc: The team visits the remote Pleasley Vale Mills. With so many victims from its industrial past, who will choose to show their displeasure as the crew roam the mill's eerie and empty corridors?

programme.title: Most Haunted: Bodelwyddan Castle, North Wales
programme.desc: Among the art and antiquities of Bodelwyddan Castle, the team discovers that some residents would rather not leave. They are prepared for a warm Welsh welcome, not a series of spine-chilling events.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Annesley Hall, Nottinghamshire
programme.desc: From style and splendor to danger and desolation, the team is horrified by the sinister secrets that Annesley Hall still harbors. Their investigation culminates in an amazing phenomenon.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Lower Southwood Cottage
programme.desc: Dating back to the 1800s, this cottage has been a part of normal family life except for hosting the RAF during WWII. What is the catalyst for a sudden influx of spiritual activity?

programme.title: Most Haunted: Castle Keep
programme.desc: One of the oldest sites the team has visited, Castle Keep was once a county jail with a number of tormented souls. Many have seen dark shadows, as well as a white light, in the gallery.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Love and Marriage - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark work to keep the three couples together.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Code Name: FREAK

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Man to Man

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Jonathan Smith Goes to Washington

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Oh Lucky Man

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Basinger's New York

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Richard Power

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Shirley Maddison

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Different Strokes
programme.desc: Zuri is a hard working single mother of two with no time or energy for herself. In a relationship with a man her own age who looks younger, she is embarrassed to be mistaken for his mother. The Glam Squad does their magic to roll back the years.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Rockin' Mom
programme.desc: Suddenly, Eva is a new wife and mother. This change in lifestyle has found her lazy and abandoning her once trendy and hip sense of style. Experts are waiting in the wings to refresh this weary mother.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Very Tall Order
programme.desc: This part-time model traded in her big city lifestyle for a family in the suburbs. Mylene's appearance has taken a backseat to her kids and full-time job. She needs a team of experts to update her look and give her a quick shot of confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hippie To Happening
programme.desc: Albert loves traveling and trying new things, except when it comes to his appearance. Albert's bad divorce has left him feeling self-conscious about the lines on his face and his graying, thinning hair.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Ground Down Mom

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Salto Mortale
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept face a new mission: performing a front-flip through the air with a stuntman on board of an estate wagon. It's a new task for coordinator and adrenaline junkie Christoph Domi Domanski.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Remote Control
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept try out another new stunt: Stuntman Tobi, aka Heidi, operates an Artega GT at full speed with a remote control. This is, however, just a warm-up before the big stunt, in which he drives a car up a steep ramp.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Graduate
programme.desc: This is what it looks like when the Stunt Heroes from Action Concept perform a long jump: a vehicle jumps at full speed over four cars, which explode one after the other. It’s a matter of precision and timing.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Very First Time
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from the Action Concept are shooting a car rollover. But stunt coordinator Carl wants to go the whole hog. His motto: if you’re going to do something at all, you might as well do it properly!

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Highfall
programme.desc: While most people never had a car crash, they know spectacular car crashes with huge explosions from movies. But these scenes are much more sensational than in real life, because cars hardly ever explode.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Behind the Scenes
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept are tough professionals. They jump from houses and make cars fly or explode. On this episode, reporter Dean Malay takes a look behind the scenes of the stunt company.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Bike stunts
programme.desc: This time the Stunt Heroes from Action Concept deal with motorbike stunts: high jumps, risky drops and dangerous crashes. As usual, stunt coordinator Domi requires his motorbike specialists Daniel and Marcel to be in top form.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Ambulance
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept are always looking for new spectacular stunts and are not running out of options. Stunt coordinator Domi’s latest idea involves an old ambulance.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Matrix
programme.desc: Martial arts specialist Ramazan creates a choreography for a fight. It involves four stuntmen who need to disguise as secret agents and bash on him. Will Ramazan be able to free himself from this uncomfortable position?

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Multiple Collision
programme.desc: Fog, darkness and a pileup involving multiple cars: It's a scene that you can often see on highways and it's a scene that the Stunt Heroes from Action Concept want to recreate as part of a stunt with burning people.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The White Army
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept leave their headquarters behind and travel to a ski resort. Between the trees of a nearby forest they simulate the attack of an army of white-dressed soldiers.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Alarm in the Ski Resort
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept are still at their ski resort and party hard. This time they prepared a spectacular stunt involving a station wagon. It is thrown 50 meters into the air with a cannon.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Body Stunt Highlights
programme.desc: Today it's Action Concepts most popular and most spectacular body stunts: Jumping from rooftops, falling of a driving car, tumbling down stairs. Despite inevitable wounds, the legendary stunt crew enjoys the job.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: East Glass/Bleaches Skin

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Make-up Addict/Obsessed with Death
programme.desc: Maureen won't go out of the house without a full face of makeup. Meanwhile, Barbara is so obsessed with death that she's planned her own funeral.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Laxatives and Pottery/Ashes

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Wears Diapers/Eats Dryer Sheets

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Rampant Rats/Extreme Fingernails
programme.desc: Theresa has more than 60 pet hairless rats that are taking over her apartment. Jazz has been growing her fingernails for 22 years. Her longest nail is two feet long, and she calls them her children.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Gas Sniffer/Teddy Bear Obsession
programme.desc: For more than 30 years, Theresa has been addicted to smelling gasoline. Meanwhile, former drug-addict Krista has 12 'children' -- all of which are teddy bears.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Off the Base
programme.desc: There’s a lot of pressure living life on a submarine—that’s why Naval Officer Jeremy Brown and his wife, Nikki, want to move out of Pearl Harbor and into the lush Hawaiian Mountains.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Turnin’ Up The Heat
programme.desc: Maui is where people come to escape. That’s exactly why Patrick and Jeannie came here from cold Massachusetts.They want to upgrade their condo for their own piece of Maui.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Jungle Fever
programme.desc: Maui’s filled with deserts by the coast and lush jungles in the mountains, many people come here to escape. Jeff and Pam want to get away from the desert and into the jungle, but will it be too wild?

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Flying Kauai
programme.desc: Gerry and Julie moved to Kauai searching for adventure. Gerry is a pilot and hang glider; he would love to find a property where he can fuse his love of excitement with functional living.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Backyard Survival
programme.desc: Life on Oahu is so expensive, for some families, the only way to get by is to grow your own food. That’s what Erik and Amy Eck want, a backyard farm to teach their baby, how to live off the land.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Volcano Living
programme.desc: The Big Island is the only place in Hawaii you’ll find active volcanoes. No matter where you are, you’re in the path of lava. Joel and Lani are willing to take the risk, but how close will they get?

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Big Island Project
programme.desc: Jesse and his wife Tracy have been living in a tent on the Big Island for three years. They’re ready to upgrade their lifestyle but still looking for a house where they can still live off the grid.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Big Apple to Big Island

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Boar Island
programme.desc: Martin and Connie came to Kauai from Los Angeles. Between the constant rain, sea creatures, and wild boars, life is rustic, but they’re here to stay, and want the perfect home for their adventure.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: One Way Ticket
programme.desc: Many people dream of living in Hawaii, and Tucker and Nicole have made that dream a reality. After huge life events, they bought one-way tickets to Oahu and are looking to put down permanent roots.

programme.title: Buying Log Cabins: Million Dollar Log Castles - THE RISKEVICH’S Minnesota
programme.desc: Kevin and Jennifer are escaping city life and looking at three one-of-a-kind log mansions. Homes offer the best views and some unique features that only Northern Minnesotans will need!
programme.sub-title: Million Dollar Log Castles - THE RISKEVICH’S Minnesota

programme.title: Buying Log Cabins: Mountain Homes - THE EMBLER’S - COLORADO
programme.desc: Matt and Genevieve are newlyweds looking to purchase their first home and they want a log cabin. They look at three different cabins offering amazing options.

programme.title: Buying RV's: Husband vs. Wife

programme.title: Buying RV's: Million Dollar RVs

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ngorongoro: Born of Fire

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Sahara: Life on the Edge
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal./After, see Africa's Dark Heart in the Congo which is seething with innumerable species./Last,learn about the largest desert in the world.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Nile: An African Odyssey
programme.desc: The Nile is the longest river in the world. Ancient Egypt, one of the history's most powerful civilizations, depended hugely upon it. Each year, it flooded, replenishing the fields with fertile silt. This automatic irrigation fueled Egypt's economy.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Philippines: Islands of Mystery
programme.desc: The Philippines are a chain of around 7,000 tropical islands in the western Pacific.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Okavango: Water in the Desert
programme.desc: The Okavango Delta, a huge emerald oasis in the burning heart of the Kalahari desert, is fed by the Okavango River and this perpetual cycle of wet and dry is the lifeblood of this extraordinary natural Eden.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ethiopia: Land of Extremes
programme.desc: Landlocked and surrounded by five countries, Ethiopia is one of east Africa's forgotten lands. Seemingly passive deserts in fact seethe with fire, and cloud-piercing peaks shield a secret Eden of canyons and cliff-tops teeming with life.

programme.title: Australia's Wild Places: The Red Desert
